      },
      "date": "2019-01-17 20:32:28.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAndreas,\n\nI did this to hopefully fix the ea_inode memory issues before https://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/34058/ (max ea size = XATTR_SIZE_MAX), so it's not needed if that patch is present.\n\nThat means this only really matters for client/server interop with an older server or if we raise ea size above XATTR_SIZE_MAX in the future.\n\nSo I'm not sure if we want this patch or not.  Your thoughts?  (If we do, I'll open a separate LU for it.)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
